22
00:18:58,955 --> 00:19:01,076
Resolution to commemorate the life of Judy Kaplan.

23
00:19:01,577 --> 00:19:08,002
Be it resolved that the Medford City Council send condolences to the friends and family of Judy Kaplan who tragically passed away on April 15th of this year.

24
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:14,887
Judy was a Medford activist, former member of the Medford Human Rights Commission, co-facilitator of a national thyroid cancer support group for over 20 years,

25
00:19:15,728 --> 00:19:23,218
Board member of the World Fellowship Center, one of the original members of SAFE Medford, and a beloved friend and colleague who touched the lives of many in our community, Councilor Lemming.

26
00:19:25,248 --> 00:19:26,548
Thank you, Council President Behrs.

27
00:19:27,829 --> 00:19:48,994
In Medford, the progressive community is pretty big and some of the younger progressives like myself and some of my colleagues have been mentored and inspired over the years by a lot of the folks who in previous generations really built up the foundation of what the progressive movement in Medford is today.

28
00:19:50,675 --> 00:19:51,895
Judy Kaplan, one of the

29
00:19:53,055 --> 00:19:59,739
Original members of Safe Medford and many of the current members are here to join us.

30
00:19:59,759 --> 00:20:12,806
A couple of them requested that we put this commemoration on the agenda, are here today.

31
00:20:12,966 --> 00:20:20,250
It's a tragedy to see folks like this go,

32
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:33,084
Knowing that she helped build up so many good movements in Medford, knowing that she was so vital to building up this community, bringing Medford into the 21st century, is touching.

33
00:20:40,330 --> 00:20:47,358
would also invite some of the folks who didn't know Judy to say a few words about their lives if they wish to.

34
00:20:47,999 --> 00:20:59,812
But at any rate, I'd like to thank folks for entertaining this resolution, and would like to also offer my condolences to Judy's friends and family.

35
00:21:00,052 --> 00:21:00,333
Thank you.

36
00:21:02,459 --> 00:21:03,620
Thank you, Councilor Lemming.

37
00:21:05,122 --> 00:21:07,824
I think you've said it well.

38
00:21:08,305 --> 00:21:15,632
Judy's loss is a loss for our city, for our community, for our activists, and for all of the people who knew and loved her.

39
00:21:16,432 --> 00:21:17,694
And we will miss her.

40
00:21:18,514 --> 00:21:23,659
If there's anyone who would like to speak about Judy now, I know some of her close friends are here.

41
00:21:24,740 --> 00:21:32,502
You have the opportunity to come to the podium or raise your hand on Zoom and we'll start at the podium if there's anyone who'd like to speak.

42
00:21:40,263 --> 00:21:40,683
Hi, Steve.

43
00:21:40,963 --> 00:21:41,983
Name and address for the record, please.

44
00:21:42,223 --> 00:21:43,304
My name is Steve Schnapp.

45
00:21:43,384 --> 00:21:45,364
I live at 36 Hillside Ave.

46
00:21:47,064 --> 00:21:49,665
And I really appreciate the council doing this.

47
00:21:51,938 --> 00:21:55,379
Judy was a friend of my wife and I for a very long time.

48
00:21:55,419 --> 00:21:57,180
My wife went to camp with her.

49
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,500
She's a camper.

50
00:21:58,961 --> 00:22:06,603
We knew her a long time and it was really great when we moved to Medford in 2011.

51
00:22:07,643 --> 00:22:13,045
Judy was a resident here and we already had friends in the community.

52
00:22:14,366 --> 00:22:17,267
She's the person who introduced me to the Human Rights Commission.

53
00:22:18,187 --> 00:22:21,148
She was a commissioner for many years, over a dozen years.

54
00:22:23,366 --> 00:22:30,368
And after the Medford Conversations project got going and Safe Medford got going, she joined that as well.

55
00:22:31,548 --> 00:22:43,411
I want to point out that this was a multi-talented person, an artist whose work in photography was displayed in City Hall.

56
00:22:46,152 --> 00:22:50,533
She was an editor of highly technical information.

57
00:22:51,465 --> 00:22:54,587
for the state and federal government.

58
00:22:55,727 --> 00:23:07,554
She was a brilliant editor, and many people relied on her for correcting their manuscripts, et cetera, including Safe Medford and the Human Rights Commission.

59
00:23:08,835 --> 00:23:11,316
And she was a stickler for details.

60
00:23:13,377 --> 00:23:15,198
And she will be missed.

61
00:23:15,698 --> 00:23:16,919
So thank you for this.

62
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:18,900
Much appreciation.

63
00:23:19,580 --> 00:23:20,201
Thank you, Steve.

64
00:23:21,285 --> 00:23:22,386
Go to Munir Germanis.

65
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:26,148
Name and address for the record, please, on Zoom.

66
00:23:28,610 --> 00:23:31,932
Munir Germanis, Three Summit Road.

67
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:42,339
I had the privilege and pleasure of working with Judy for several years on the Human Rights Commission.

68
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:48,623
Her work and participation in this commission were beyond compare.

69
00:23:49,502 --> 00:23:57,165
She was always honest, forthright, and respectful as a key member of the commission for many, many years.

70
00:23:58,286 --> 00:24:08,630
She was also an invaluable resource during the process of generating a new human rights commission ordinance that was passed last year.

71
00:24:08,650 --> 00:24:12,352
I, for one, will certainly miss her.

72
00:24:13,612 --> 00:24:14,433
Godspeed, Judy.

73
00:24:15,033 --> 00:24:15,373
Thank you.

74
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:18,360
Thank you, Muneer.

75
00:24:19,081 --> 00:24:20,562
Recognize Eileen Lerner on Zoom.

76
00:24:29,027 --> 00:24:34,990
I met Judy over 40 years ago up in New Hampshire at World Fellowship.

77
00:24:37,612 --> 00:24:38,913
And we became friends.

78
00:24:40,534 --> 00:24:45,477
We had mutual friends and mutual interests and

79
00:24:46,610 --> 00:25:01,617
When I moved to Medford 12 years ago, it brought me into greater contact with Judy on the Human Rights Commission and in various activities in Medford.

80
00:25:02,737 --> 00:25:04,258
I greatly admired her.

81
00:25:04,278 --> 00:25:12,682
I was grateful to her for her editing of my writing, which she did for free.

82
00:25:13,982 --> 00:25:15,403
And I learned a lot from her.

83
00:25:17,355 --> 00:25:20,618
And this is a great loss.

84
00:25:20,858 --> 00:25:21,699
I will miss her.

85
00:25:23,761 --> 00:25:25,242
And I know we all will miss her.

86
00:25:26,143 --> 00:25:34,750
And I do want to thank the city council for giving us this opportunity to express our feelings about this loss.

87
00:25:35,811 --> 00:25:36,291
Thank you.

88
00:25:38,733 --> 00:25:39,374
Thank you, Eileen.

89
00:25:47,343 --> 00:25:49,445
Ellen Epstein, 15 Grove Street.

90
00:25:50,786 --> 00:26:02,555
I'm just going to be brief and say that I think the thing we can do to best commemorate Judy and her life is to get the Human Rights Commission up and running again.

91
00:26:04,096 --> 00:26:04,577
Thank you.

92
00:26:05,697 --> 00:26:06,318
Thank you, Ellen.

