01:49:01,023 --> 01:49:05,266
26081 fiscal 25 prior year unpaid bill for public schools.

1100
01:49:05,366 --> 01:49:07,688
Dear President Piers and city councilors, I respectfully recommend.

1101
01:49:08,870 --> 01:49:26,043
Request to recommend that your honorable body approve the expenditure of fiscal year 2027 school department appropriations in the amount of $48,866.17 for the payment of prior fiscal year bills in accordance with Mass General Law Chapter 44, Section 64 as detailed in the enclosed documents respectfully submitted.

1102
01:49:26,484 --> 01:49:27,785
Brigadier General Gohern, Mayor.

1103
01:49:28,325 --> 01:49:28,986
We have a further.

1104
01:49:30,288 --> 01:49:35,615
Memorandum from Chief Operating Officer Ken Lord to Finance Director Noel Velez.

1105
01:49:35,975 --> 01:49:37,597
Gone Green unpaid bill, date April 1, 2026.

1106
01:49:38,098 --> 01:49:41,963
We've received invoices totaling $48,866.17 from our electrical fire alarm contractor, Gone Green, from fiscal year 25 and earlier.

1107
01:49:49,432 --> 01:49:53,334
We completed the work and received invoices via email, and the invoices were never processed for payment.

1108
01:49:53,754 --> 01:49:57,876
It's unclear if failing to process these invoices was because of facilities or accounts payable to staff error.

1109
01:49:58,396 --> 01:50:01,237
Gone Green sent the invoices but never followed up on payment until now.

1110
01:50:01,297 --> 01:50:04,398
I'd recommend that we request permission to pay these invoices from this year's budget.

1111
01:50:04,838 --> 01:50:09,160
I met with our staff and facilities to discuss the process and procedures for ensuring they properly pay invoices.

1112
01:50:09,580 --> 01:50:13,682
They had already implemented improved record keeping this year prior to these overdue invoices being discovered.

1113
01:50:14,089 --> 01:50:18,393
Going forward, we'll implement a process of regularly checking in with vendors to ensure they receive and pay invoices.

1114
01:50:18,413 --> 01:50:20,034
Let me know if you have any questions.

1115
01:50:20,594 --> 01:50:21,515
I'll turn it over to you guys.

1116
01:50:22,136 --> 01:50:29,162
So as the memo is written, we were notified of these invoices being unpaid.

1117
01:50:29,242 --> 01:50:32,685
It was quite a shock to us that they had never asked for payment usually.

1118
01:50:33,265 --> 01:50:34,646
You know, they're beating down the doors for a check.

1119
01:50:34,666 --> 01:50:37,247
It's really, we did an investigation.

1120
01:50:37,267 --> 01:50:39,349
It's really unclear where the failure point was.

1121
01:50:39,849 --> 01:50:47,193
Prior to these coming in, they had already started doing better record keeping, tracking of invoices, checking to make sure things were paid.

1122
01:50:48,074 --> 01:50:50,275
So we've done an investigation.

1123
01:50:50,335 --> 01:50:54,437
We've put extra precautions in place to make sure this does not happen again.

1124
01:50:55,498 --> 01:50:57,019
But we do owe this money.

1125
01:50:57,219 --> 01:50:59,040
It has been verified this work was completed.

1126
01:50:59,872 --> 01:51:03,734
This was presented to the school committee and they did approve, but we also need your approval as well.

1127
01:51:06,034 --> 01:51:06,755
