1485
02:16:45,933 --> 02:16:46,313
Sure.

1486
02:16:47,014 --> 02:16:52,456
So actually, I had our intern, Paul Christian, has been wonderful.

1487
02:16:53,136 --> 02:16:59,579
So overall, he found that we had had 16 public meetings focused on Medford Square.

1488
02:16:59,779 --> 02:17:02,341
Some were joint with West Medford from back then.

1489
02:17:02,961 --> 02:17:06,663
We've had five public information sessions.

1490
02:17:07,743 --> 02:17:13,346
And we've actually had 99 written and verbal public comments specifically about the squares.

1491
02:17:14,967 --> 02:17:20,210
And then if you were to include all the general zoning comments, we actually had 225.

1492
02:17:22,232 --> 02:17:27,335
But these were specifically for the squares between both last summer and now.

1493
02:17:28,196 --> 02:17:37,822
And this most recent, we had four joint City Council Community Development Board joint hearings.

1494
02:17:39,223 --> 02:17:50,269
three public information sessions, one at the Senior Center during the day, one at the McGlynn School at night, and one morning during a snowstorm on Zoom with the Chamber of Commerce.

1495
02:17:50,309 --> 02:17:52,910
We were going to go in person until we had a blizzard.

1496
02:17:54,270 --> 02:18:02,674
And then the Community Development Board had a couple of working sessions with the consultant, where they just sort of got some better understanding and worked through some things.

1497
02:18:03,114 --> 02:18:12,098
But then they had one, they had on May 15, April 15, their public hearing, that was the, where they made these final recommendations.

1498
02:18:12,198 --> 02:18:22,283
And their recommendation was unanimously to adopt this version of the map in the zoning language that is on the City Council agenda tonight.

1499
02:18:26,317 --> 02:18:27,219
All right, Councilor Lemming.

1500
02:18:29,103 --> 02:18:29,885
I wasn't tracking.

1501
02:18:29,905 --> 02:18:35,578
Did that include the internal meetings that we had about this, that count that we just had?

1502
02:18:36,083 --> 02:18:38,225
No, those were just the public meetings.

1503
02:18:39,046 --> 02:18:39,366
Oh, OK.

1504
02:18:39,486 --> 02:18:44,792
I did not actually go back and check how many internal meetings because, you know, we have.

1505
02:18:45,672 --> 02:18:56,042
Would you count the times that we sat around the planning office talking with the staff between ourselves before we made comments to other people as well as as internal meetings?

1506
02:18:56,863 --> 02:18:57,023
Yeah.

1507
02:18:57,063 --> 02:18:58,345
These were just the public meetings.

1508
02:18:59,338 --> 02:19:01,799
Yeah, sorry, I'm just beating a dead horse here.

1509
02:19:02,180 --> 02:19:20,590
And this also, what we also need to consider is the many, many meetings that went into the Medford Comprehensive Plan as well as the previous plans that were made in, I believe, 2005 and 2017 for reimagining Medford Square.

1510
02:19:20,630 --> 02:19:21,310
So there has been,

1511
02:19:29,123 --> 02:19:41,948
quite a bit of thought and effort behind this, and I'm glad that we are finally at the finish line for this particular piece of zoning.

1512
02:19:43,728 --> 02:19:45,469
Once again, it's late.

1513
02:19:45,829 --> 02:19:47,970
We've had a lot of discussion on this.

1514
02:19:48,030 --> 02:19:48,850
I have a motion to approve.

1515
02:19:48,870 --> 02:19:50,791
All right.

1516
02:19:50,991 --> 02:19:53,292
Do we have any further discussion by members of the council?

1517
02:19:53,312 --> 02:19:53,652
Councilor Sang.

1518
02:19:55,397 --> 02:19:56,358
Thank you, President Behrs.

1519
02:19:57,078 --> 02:20:04,824
First, I want to thank our Planning, Development, and Sustainability Department, NS Associates, and the Community Development Board for their work on this.

1520
02:20:05,645 --> 02:20:13,110
These weren't always easy conversations, but they were thoughtful ones, and I think this proposal is stronger because of that engagement.

1521
02:20:13,851 --> 02:20:22,858
I think as we have noted tonight and many times before, this has been years in the making, and we're finally meeting a major milestone.

1522
02:20:23,930 --> 02:20:29,378
When we knock on doors here in Medford, people don't usually come up to us talking about zoning.

1523
02:20:30,399 --> 02:20:34,785
But they do ask why their kids can't afford to live in the city where they grew up.

1524
02:20:35,613 --> 02:20:42,155
They ask why storefronts in the square sit empty for years and why this square doesn't feel as bustling as it can be.

1525
02:20:42,675 --> 02:20:45,495
They see that Medford Square has real potential.

1526
02:20:45,815 --> 02:20:51,157
And we can all feel it when we walk by Mrs. Murphy's, Alta Cuba, Deep Cuts.

1527
02:20:52,337 --> 02:20:56,318
But we also all know that the bigger picture isn't quite there yet.

1528
02:20:56,958 --> 02:20:59,759
So they ask why a place they love can feel stuck.

1529
02:21:00,519 --> 02:21:05,220
And often the same breath, they'll say that they love Medford Square's historic character,

1530
02:21:05,860 --> 02:21:08,441
It's neighborhood feel, and that's what makes it special.

1531
02:21:10,362 --> 02:21:12,122
I don't see these as competing values.

1532
02:21:12,342 --> 02:21:19,305
I see all of this as one community asking us to do both, and that's exactly what this proposal tries to deliver.

1533
02:21:21,165 --> 02:21:29,148
I want to push back on the framing that this is some binary choice between growth or preservation, new housing or neighborhood character.

1534
02:21:30,089 --> 02:21:33,810
I don't think it has to be, and I'd go further saying that

1535
02:21:34,747 --> 02:21:37,589
Doing nothing has never been a neutral option.

1536
02:21:38,269 --> 02:21:54,798
Our zoning status quo was itself a choice, a choice that came with real costs for young people being priced out, for small businesses trying to survive on the block without enough foot traffic, for downtown that has the bones to be something great and hasn't been allowed to get there yet.

1537
02:21:55,739 --> 02:21:57,580
This ordinance says yes and.

1538
02:21:58,280 --> 02:22:02,543
Yes to more housing while protecting surrounding neighborhoods with mandatory step backs,

1539
02:22:03,407 --> 02:22:05,528
landscape buffers and sunlight protections.

1540
02:22:06,228 --> 02:22:09,310
Yes to additional height, but not as a giveaway to developers.

1541
02:22:09,810 --> 02:22:17,554
We say yes when our community gets more affordable units, more public space, more support for local businesses and nonprofits.

1542
02:22:18,454 --> 02:22:22,336
That's very intentionally designed into this ordinance and it matters.

1543
02:22:23,997 --> 02:22:30,360
This ordinance says yes to new growth and yes to preserving what makes Medford Square worth growing.

1544
02:22:31,609 --> 02:22:36,730
This plan makes it easier to adaptively reuse our historic buildings and not tear them down.

1545
02:22:37,150 --> 02:22:42,692
Because we recognize that a square that loses its history in the name of development isn't a success.

1546
02:22:43,172 --> 02:22:46,733
But a square that stays frozen in the name of preservation isn't one either.

1547
02:22:46,753 --> 02:22:50,494
We're saying yes to finally taking advantage of what's coming.

1548
02:22:51,114 --> 02:23:00,376
Medford Square is on track to become a real transit hub with increased bus service, direct connections to the T. And that's a once in a generation opportunity.

1549
02:23:00,988 --> 02:23:07,372
But transit-oriented development only works when people actually live nearby, when people actually can get connected.

1550
02:23:08,112 --> 02:23:16,878
It works when businesses have a customer base, and this plan gives us the tools to build one right where we need it most.

1551
02:23:18,599 --> 02:23:26,184
A city that can't make room for future generations or for the people who already built their lives here isn't preserving something.

1552
02:23:26,384 --> 02:23:27,665
It's deciding who gets to stay.

1553
02:23:28,730 --> 02:23:31,312
And I don't think that's the Medford we want to be.

1554
02:23:31,933 --> 02:23:35,656
We can welcome growth and we can protect what people love about this place.

1555
02:23:35,956 --> 02:23:37,658
We don't have to choose between one or the other.

1556
02:23:37,698 --> 02:23:40,040
We can choose good planning and good governance instead.

1557
02:23:40,735 --> 02:23:46,000
We've worked really hard to get to this point, and I'm really proud of the work that we've accomplished.

1558
02:23:46,080 --> 02:23:54,889
I know people have feelings about this not going far enough or going too far, but I think this shows an earnest effort to listen to everyone.

1559
02:23:56,190 --> 02:23:58,612
And I would encourage everyone to vote yes tonight.

1560
02:24:01,975 --> 02:24:02,876
Thank you, Councilor Sang.

1561
02:24:02,896 --> 02:24:05,419
I definitely share a lot of the

1562
02:24:06,523 --> 02:24:08,223
thoughts that you brought forward.

1563
02:24:08,624 --> 02:24:15,125
And I think one thing we just need to be aware of is we're putting this into place and then we're going to see if it works.

1564
02:24:15,145 --> 02:24:25,948
And if we don't see the kind of growth and change that we want to see or if there are pieces of it that need to be adjusted, then we need to continue to iterate and update and improve our zoning.

1565
02:24:26,028 --> 02:24:28,509
So we're going to have something to work through.

1566
02:24:28,529 --> 02:24:30,730
We're going to have something to help us

1567
02:24:32,153 --> 02:24:35,516
build a new future for Medford Square and it's come out of a lot of work.

1568
02:24:36,176 --> 02:24:47,705
And I really hope that it's the start of a continued commitment to regularly look at our zoning to make sure that we are building the types of buildings that we want to see here in our city.

1569
02:24:47,925 --> 02:24:48,626
Councilor Scarpelli.

1570
02:24:51,027 --> 02:25:01,055
Again, to elaborate what Councilor Lemming was saying, I think that what he was bringing forward was the concerns we had and we heard at the beginning of the process is that we just weren't listening.

1571
02:25:02,791 --> 02:25:08,293
And we weren't bringing the information to the neighborhoods.

1572
02:25:08,333 --> 02:25:29,838
And I think that working with our partners in the Community Development Board and listening to their expertise and really, for me, what really excited me is the fact that the people that have to listen to the process, and that's our Community Development Board, and understand what

1573
02:25:30,538 --> 02:25:47,213
the hurdles were and the differences were and bringing everybody together in a meeting and sharing those thoughts and then listening to community members and really bringing those meetings to them and then bringing it back over and over again.

1574
02:25:47,233 --> 02:25:56,041
I think that we have really a true picture of what everybody who wanted to be part of the process

1575
02:25:56,883 --> 02:25:58,604
took advantage of being part of the process.

1576
02:25:59,324 --> 02:26:10,291
And that's why I feel comfortable today that is it in everybody's eyes the best options?

1577
02:26:10,591 --> 02:26:10,871
No.

1578
02:26:11,571 --> 02:26:12,812
Still hear it from both sides.

1579
02:26:13,393 --> 02:26:16,995
But the bottom line is this is what democracy is about.

1580
02:26:17,115 --> 02:26:22,658
This is what the process that we were talking about at the beginning and that I first

1581
02:26:23,427 --> 02:26:38,601
complain so much about but I appreciate for this council to work together and partner with the Community Development Board and then really work with Alicia Hunt and bringing the team together and then bringing it out to the public and listening to everybody.

1582
02:26:38,641 --> 02:26:46,208
I mean something simple as just the map in front of us and understanding the different color codes so it's understood

1583
02:26:47,996 --> 02:26:52,323
for the common person, that it makes it a little bit easier, makes a huge difference.

1584
02:26:52,363 --> 02:26:56,711
So that's why I'll be supporting this, and I hope everybody follows suit.

1585
02:26:56,731 --> 02:26:57,612
So thank you, Mr. President.

1586
02:27:01,832 --> 02:27:02,913
There was a motion at some point.

1587
02:27:03,213 --> 02:27:04,014
I can't remember who made it.

1588
02:27:04,994 --> 02:27:05,675
It was Councilor Lemming?

1589
02:27:05,695 --> 02:27:05,755
Yes.

1590
02:27:06,255 --> 02:27:08,677
The clerk actually just asked him before I said that out loud.

1591
02:27:08,797 --> 02:27:12,280
I would have sounded so much smarter if I'd asked our acting clerk, Alicio.

1592
02:27:13,361 --> 02:27:23,069
Councilor Lemming made a motion to approve the version accepting all of the recommendations of the Community Development Board as well as the zoning map and ordained the Medford Square District.

1593
02:27:24,270 --> 02:27:24,450
Great.

1594
02:27:25,652 --> 02:27:39,257
So it's a motion to accept the recommendations of the Community Development Board and adopt the proposed Medford Square zoning district ordinance and map to be ordained, seconded by Councilor Sang.

1595
02:27:40,437 --> 02:27:42,078
Any further discussion by members of the council?

1596
02:27:43,718 --> 02:27:45,179
Any discussion by members of the public?

1597
02:27:47,559 --> 02:27:49,040
I see a Community Development Board member.

1598
02:27:49,100 --> 02:27:50,280
I don't know if you want to share anything.

1599
02:27:50,300 --> 02:27:51,341
You don't have to, no pressure.

1600
02:27:53,658 --> 02:27:54,299
Thumbs up.

1601
02:27:54,339 --> 02:27:55,840
We got a thumbs up.

1602
02:27:56,381 --> 02:27:56,701
All right.

1603
02:27:58,263 --> 02:28:00,505
On the motion, Mr. Clerk, please call the roll.

1604
02:28:01,947 --> 02:28:02,667
Councilor Callahan?

1605
02:28:02,687 --> 02:28:02,748
Yes.

1606
02:28:04,089 --> 02:28:04,730
Councilor Leving?

1607
02:28:04,750 --> 02:28:06,111
Yes.

1608
02:28:06,131 --> 02:28:06,672
Councilor Mullain?

1609
02:28:06,692 --> 02:28:06,752
Yes.

1610
02:28:08,133 --> 02:28:08,914
Councilor Scarpelli?

1611
02:28:08,934 --> 02:28:09,014
Yes.

1612
02:28:10,155 --> 02:28:10,676
Councilor Singh?

1613
02:28:10,696 --> 02:28:10,756
Yes.

1614
02:28:11,797 --> 02:28:12,538
Vice President Lazaro?

1615
02:28:12,558 --> 02:28:12,698
Yes.

1616
02:28:14,543 --> 02:28:15,123
President Beers.

1617
02:28:15,523 --> 02:28:18,184
Yes, I'm in the affirmative, none the negative, the motion passes.

1618
02:28:19,024 --> 02:28:21,885
Medford Square Zoning District is ordained.

1619
02:28:23,045 --> 02:28:23,585
Great job, everybody.

1620
02:28:23,605 --> 02:28:24,705
Thank you and have a good evening.

1621
02:28:25,506 --> 02:28:26,326
Thank you, Director Hunt.

1622
02:28:28,906 --> 02:28:35,788
All right, 25189 offered by President Beers, amendment to chapter two, article five, division two, Medford standard compensation ordinance.

1623
02:28:35,828 --> 02:28:43,010
So we met on this in committee of the whole two weeks ago, and there was a motion to refer out the version as amended by

1624
02:28:44,964 --> 02:28:52,709
myself based on, you know, we had, I think it's now version 5 but this is the version that includes many of the items that we wanted to see.

1625
02:28:52,750 --> 02:29:13,424
We had a pretty robust discussion somewhat on the merits of this ordinance, you know, at least to start and then we got a little sidetracked and distracted by some, I don't even know how to characterize it but, you know, what do they call that, the dog wagging the tail, the tail wagging the dog?

1626
02:29:15,198 --> 02:29:30,984
And what we have before us tonight, we had a pretty extensive discussion and we also heard from legal experts and others who said this is something that we see in other communities and is, you know, more than within our authority to implement.

1627
02:29:31,084 --> 02:29:33,084
So, that's where we're at.

1628
02:29:33,645 --> 02:29:35,625
I don't think we've received further communications.

1629
02:29:35,645 --> 02:29:37,546
I don't know if there's any other councilors.

1630
02:29:37,606 --> 02:29:39,067
I know Councilor Seng made that motion.

1631
02:29:39,087 --> 02:29:41,027
Other councilors spoke if they want to speak to this.

1632
02:29:41,867 --> 02:29:42,928
I am the lead sponsor.

1633
02:29:43,908 --> 02:29:47,411
And I did, you know, do the initial drafting and the latest draft.

1634
02:29:47,491 --> 02:29:55,698
So if there's anything other councilors want to add, my feeling is to move to a first reading, but I will go to Councilor Sang.

1635
02:29:57,237 --> 02:29:59,078
I would recommend moving to first reading as well.

1636
02:29:59,198 --> 02:30:00,098
I'll make that motion.

1637
02:30:00,118 --> 02:30:02,659
I strongly support this ordinance.

1638
02:30:02,919 --> 02:30:11,081
I think, I mean, I've kind of said this at the committee, the whole meeting a few weeks ago, or when we last met on it.

1639
02:30:11,961 --> 02:30:15,162
I think at the core, this is about a pretty simple principle.

1640
02:30:15,262 --> 02:30:22,444
It's about saying that when our city spends public dollars, those dollars shouldn't drive down labor standards.

1641
02:30:23,344 --> 02:30:25,365
We should be in charge of uplifting them.

1642
02:30:27,323 --> 02:30:33,525
I know it was a sensitive kind of moment when the school district switched janitorial contractors.

1643
02:30:33,905 --> 02:30:38,347
A lot of the workers who'd done this work for years lost their jobs overnight.

1644
02:30:38,827 --> 02:30:43,288
And they were replaced by workers who were making less with fewer protections as well.

1645
02:30:44,872 --> 02:30:46,653
That happened right here in Medford.

1646
02:30:47,113 --> 02:30:50,314
And it happened because we didn't have a floor.

1647
02:30:51,335 --> 02:30:59,758
And I think it's really important to say plainly that too often it can be easy in government to reduce workers to line items on a spreadsheet.

1648
02:31:00,518 --> 02:31:01,739
But these are people.

1649
02:31:02,439 --> 02:31:03,780
They're people supporting families.

1650
02:31:04,000 --> 02:31:07,461
They're people paying rent in an increasingly expensive region.

1651
02:31:08,321 --> 02:31:11,703
They're people who are doing essential work that keeps our city running.

1652
02:31:12,763 --> 02:31:15,064
And this ordinance really recognizes that.

1653
02:31:16,245 --> 02:31:24,469
If you say you contract with the city, there are basic standards that you'll have to meet around wages, benefits, paid leave, creating a floor.

1654
02:31:25,790 --> 02:31:37,657
And just as importantly, it's about including transparency and enforcement into the process, because we can set standards, but without accountability, it doesn't mean very much.

1655
02:31:39,007 --> 02:31:44,793
I think this is, at the end of the day, really just about what role we want our local governments to play.

1656
02:31:45,753 --> 02:31:50,897
We should be using public dollars to support decent work and to strengthen the community we all serve.

1657
02:31:51,738 --> 02:31:56,121
And it's not some abstract ideological statement to say that.

1658
02:31:56,442 --> 02:31:59,304
It's practical, it's fair, and it's overdue.

1659
02:32:01,866 --> 02:32:08,852
Our city should stand up and say that we value the people whose labor keeps this place running, who've built the city and made it what it is.

1660
02:32:11,244 --> 02:32:17,307
I'll, again, motion to approve this for first reading and I urge my colleagues to support it too.

1661
02:32:17,327 --> 02:32:20,228
Thank you, Councilor Sang.

1662
02:32:20,268 --> 02:32:21,088
Councilor Callahan.

1663
02:32:22,809 --> 02:32:23,169
Thank you.

1664
02:32:24,510 --> 02:32:27,671
I do appreciate all the work that everyone has done on this.

1665
02:32:28,252 --> 02:32:33,534
I just want to tie in a little bit the relationship between democracy and inequality.

1666
02:32:33,554 --> 02:32:39,817
You know, in urban planning graduate school many years ago, inequality was my primary focus.

1667
02:32:41,137 --> 02:32:48,887
And one thing that people who study inequality understand is that when inequality gets really high, that's when democracies fail.

1668
02:32:51,109 --> 02:32:57,557
And I think we are in a moment right now where our inequality in the United States is

1669
02:32:59,579 --> 02:33:06,022
higher than it was in 1929, which is the highest that it had been for a hundred years.

1670
02:33:06,843 --> 02:33:22,552
So I think it's really imperative that as a society we think about these things more carefully and we don't allow ourselves to get into situations like what we are in now.

1671
02:33:24,413 --> 02:33:28,836
You know, all the pressure on every city is to pay less and less and less.

1672
02:33:28,936 --> 02:33:31,478
All the pressure on every company is to pay less and less and less.

1673
02:33:32,478 --> 02:33:40,503
And unfortunately, there are dire consequences, not just for the people who are being paid so little, but on all of us.

1674
02:33:40,844 --> 02:33:42,285
So I will be supporting this.

1675
02:33:42,305 --> 02:33:42,605
Thank you.

1676
02:33:42,625 --> 02:33:45,387
Thank you, Councilor Callahan.

1677
02:33:45,407 --> 02:33:49,089
We have a motion from Councilor Sang to approve for first reading, seconded by.

1678
02:33:50,350 --> 02:33:51,811
Seconded by Councilor Callahan.

1679
02:33:51,851 --> 02:33:53,612
Is there any further discussion by members of the council?

1680
02:33:57,061 --> 02:34:01,263
Seeing none, any further discussion by members of the public, either in person or on Zoom.

1681
02:34:04,764 --> 02:34:07,325
See our former facilities director, Paul Riggi.

1682
02:34:07,445 --> 02:34:09,406
Paul, name and address for the record, please.

1683
02:34:12,988 --> 02:34:17,350
Paul Riggi, former director of facilities for the city of Medford.

1684
02:34:18,676 --> 02:34:20,918
I just have a couple of questions.

1685
02:34:22,480 --> 02:34:32,608
For clarification, this was the version of this draft ordinance that was redlined during the Committee of the Whole meeting.

1686
02:34:32,628 --> 02:34:34,049
Is that correct?

1687
02:34:34,850 --> 02:34:35,010
Yes.

1688
02:34:35,931 --> 02:34:44,638
Was this version of the ordinance reviewed by city legal counsel or legal counsel representative for the city of Medford?

1689
02:34:45,637 --> 02:34:47,538
It was submitted to council.

1690
02:34:48,418 --> 02:34:50,359
We haven't received a reply for several weeks.

1691
02:34:51,719 --> 02:34:52,379
This version?

1692
02:34:53,680 --> 02:34:53,960
Yes.

1693
02:34:55,780 --> 02:34:56,101
Okay.

1694
02:35:00,882 --> 02:35:01,302
Thank you.

1695
02:35:02,423 --> 02:35:02,723
Thank you.

1696
02:35:11,286 --> 02:35:11,526
All right.

1697
02:35:13,066 --> 02:35:16,727
Seeing no further discussion on the motion to approve for first reading, Mr. Clerk, please call the roll.

1698
02:35:18,728 --> 02:35:19,508
Councilor Callahan?

1699
02:35:19,528 --> 02:35:19,588
Yes.

1700
02:35:21,629 --> 02:35:22,289
Councilor Lemming?

1701
02:35:22,309 --> 02:35:23,650
Yes.

1702
02:35:23,670 --> 02:35:24,170
Councilor Malayne?

1703
02:35:24,190 --> 02:35:24,310
Yes.

1704
02:35:25,610 --> 02:35:26,291
Councilor Scarpelli?

1705
02:35:26,311 --> 02:35:26,431
Yes.

1706
02:35:27,531 --> 02:35:28,171
Councilor Singh?

1707
02:35:28,271 --> 02:35:28,411
Yes.

1708
02:35:29,392 --> 02:35:30,092
Vice President Lazaro?

1709
02:35:30,112 --> 02:35:30,192
Yes.

1710
02:35:31,272 --> 02:35:31,832
President Pierce?

1711
02:35:32,413 --> 02:35:32,633
Yes.

1712
02:35:33,513 --> 02:35:35,994
Assembly affirmative, none of the negative, the motion passes.

1713
02:35:37,354 --> 02:35:59,869
26077 offered by President Behrs, Councilor Scarpelli, and Councilor Sang, resolution to file a public records request for comprehensive litigation report due to the administration's failure to respond to Resolution 26043, whereas on February 24th, 2026, the Medford City Council unanimously voted to approve Council Resolution 26043 to request that the mayoral administration produce a comprehensive litigation report on all legal matters since 2019.

1714
02:36:01,210 --> 02:36:07,252
And whereas in spite of the council's resolution and over 60 days having passed for the administration to reply, the administration has not responded.

1715
02:36:07,392 --> 02:36:12,814
And whereas President Obama said, quote, the Freedom of Information Act should be administered with a clear presumption.

1716
02:36:12,974 --> 02:36:14,795
In the face of doubt, openness prevails.

1717
02:36:15,235 --> 02:36:24,578
The government should not keep information confidential merely because public officials might be embarrassed by disclosure, because errors and failures might be revealed, or because of speculative or abstract fears.

1718
02:36:25,198 --> 02:36:52,746
And, whereas the residents of Medford who fund our city government through taxes and fees deserve to know how money is being spent and whether the administration's strategic and procedural approach to litigation is prudent and effective, now, therefore, be it resolved by the Medford City Council that we, as a body, make a request for public records to the City of Medford under the provisions of the Massachusetts Public Records Act, General Law, Chapter 66, Section 10, asking that the city produce records pertaining to all lawsuits, claims, administrative proceedings, arbitration proceedings,

1719
02:36:53,242 --> 02:37:00,824
and or other legal actions in which the city of Medford and or Brianna Lungo Kern in her capacity as mayor of the city of Medford is or was a named party.

1720
02:37:01,264 --> 02:37:07,286
Be it further resolved that we respectfully request that our colleagues on the council support this resolution and the draft public records request attached.

1721
02:37:08,206 --> 02:37:10,347
There's attached public records request.

1722
02:37:10,487 --> 02:37:12,067
I encourage folks to read it.

1723
02:37:12,227 --> 02:37:13,468
It's about four pages long.

1724
02:37:15,068 --> 02:37:21,930
It's also available as part of the agenda on the website, but I'm just going to read the resolution for now.

1725
02:37:23,052 --> 02:37:30,179
And this is a response to our resolution February 24th where we requested a comprehensive litigation report.

1726
02:37:30,900 --> 02:37:34,723
The council did receive an email today at 3 something p.m., 3.13 p.m.

1727
02:37:39,133 --> 02:37:40,473
I'm writing on the above resolution.

1728
02:37:40,513 --> 02:37:48,376
As you know, this is an especially busy period with the budget season, MSBA zoning, Medford Square, and trying to keep pace with the council.

1729
02:37:48,876 --> 02:37:53,918
We wanted to let you know that we have begun reviewing the council's resolution as part of comprehensive litigation review.

1730
02:37:54,438 --> 02:37:56,719
The attached document was prepared in connection with the process.

1731
02:37:56,759 --> 02:38:01,260
Of course, the council may proceed as it sees fit with the new resolution, but I wanted to make you aware.

1732
02:38:02,035 --> 02:38:15,838
that we've been working on this and they attached a document that is essentially just a summary of the resolution we sent them two months ago and not necessarily an accurate summary of that resolution.

1733
02:38:16,118 --> 02:38:26,020
So they turned our resolution back into bullet points and we found that out today at 3-15, two months after our resolution.

1734
02:38:28,440 --> 02:38:35,622
I have some issues with the idea that they're, this is a good faith and timely response to our resolution.

1735
02:38:36,102 --> 02:38:39,504
With that, I'll turn it over to my colleagues, Councilor Scarpelli and then Councilor Singh.

1736
02:38:40,544 --> 02:38:40,884
Thank you.

1737
02:38:41,924 --> 02:38:43,225
Thank you, Mr. President.

1738
02:38:44,265 --> 02:38:53,428
I felt like my frustration earlier played a big part of what we're dealing with this and, you know, the communication we're getting with the Chief of Staff.

1739
02:38:55,728 --> 02:39:00,111
I want the public to realize that this doesn't normally happen in other communities.

1740
02:39:00,331 --> 02:39:07,295
You have an administration that actually works hand-in-hand with your city council and your school committee to

1741
02:39:09,940 --> 02:39:14,544
to support the best course of action for your community and the way we're spending our money especially.

1742
02:39:15,705 --> 02:39:30,838
I felt this is important that we move this forward to the FOIA request for the fact that I couldn't vote for the budget in the coming weeks and months that if we don't know the true picture of where our money is being spent,

1743
02:39:31,959 --> 02:39:43,148
I've been on the soapbox for many years now asking about and pleading for a breakdown and unfortunately it's taken us to this point right now.

1744
02:39:44,348 --> 02:40:06,931
when you're seeing over 500% increase in lawsuits dealing with our own labor force, and you're seeing processes where the administration brings this to arbitration or bring this to court and they lose, but then follow up with an appeal knowing that it won't win.

1745
02:40:08,472 --> 02:40:17,575
And as we're seeing more and more information, as we're going to more and more executive meetings and looking at the money that we're being spent, we're not seeing the true picture.

1746
02:40:17,595 --> 02:40:18,615
And what is the true picture?

1747
02:40:19,315 --> 02:40:23,276
Let's say we settle on a lawsuit of $50,000.

1748
02:40:24,317 --> 02:40:35,660
What we're not seeing is the cost of the legal fees for our attorney, but then the legal fees for the opposing attorneys.

1749
02:40:36,560 --> 02:40:49,294
And then we're hearing facts that our part of these discussions or situations are being investigated by private investigators.

1750
02:40:49,374 --> 02:40:53,558
And in many years, I haven't seen a line for private investigators fees.

1751
02:40:54,259 --> 02:40:58,384
And these are the things that are now popping up and becoming prevalent in the fact that

1752
02:40:59,368 --> 02:41:01,289
We want to know where our money is going.

1753
02:41:02,110 --> 02:41:08,093
And we've been asking, and we've been asking politely, we've been asking the process, and it just doesn't come out.

1754
02:41:09,093 --> 02:41:21,941
And to my frustration today, we've always, with the former finance director, Alicia Nunley, she used to give us a report that our finance director has now, it's the same system.

1755
02:41:22,747 --> 02:41:28,190
And she would give us a breakdown on a monthly basis of what our actuals were that month.

1756
02:41:28,230 --> 02:41:31,472
So we at least knew what we were paying out.

1757
02:41:32,212 --> 02:41:39,737
And we would at least have the opportunity to ask questions where we're spending our money, the city's money, our residents' money, right?

1758
02:41:40,517 --> 02:41:41,538
We don't even see that.

1759
02:41:43,739 --> 02:41:50,263
The fact then to get this email today at 315 saying that we're working on it because we're working so hard.

1760
02:41:51,617 --> 02:41:53,879
Here's a hint to the administration.

1761
02:41:54,939 --> 02:41:59,763
Hire a city solicitor and our chief of staff wouldn't have to worry about doing this.

1762
02:42:00,783 --> 02:42:01,844
It's not your job.

1763
02:42:04,026 --> 02:42:06,888
But again, these are the issues that we're having.

1764
02:42:06,988 --> 02:42:16,855
Think of the hours that have to go through to do this for us now from a person that's really not qualified to do it.

1765
02:42:20,301 --> 02:42:21,822
The city solicitor does this.

1766
02:42:21,882 --> 02:42:22,983
This is their job.

1767
02:42:23,903 --> 02:42:39,874
And it's a shame that we have to go to these lengths to get information so we can answer to the constituents that voted us into this position to say, yes, this is where the money's going, and we have proof of this, and let's move on.

1768
02:42:40,354 --> 02:42:40,954
That's all it is.

1769
02:42:40,974 --> 02:42:43,796
Because I've said this 1,000 times.

1770
02:42:43,936 --> 02:42:46,218
I'm not saying anybody's doing anything illegal.

1771
02:42:47,287 --> 02:42:53,932
What I'm saying is, over and over again, we're seeing mismanagement of the city's finances.

1772
02:42:57,394 --> 02:43:06,900
Now, this just isn't KP law, so what we got back today was just, it was, like Council President said, it was a list of what we asked for, but it wasn't just that.

1773
02:43:07,801 --> 02:43:10,863
What we're asking in this request goes deeper.

1774
02:43:12,244 --> 02:43:16,347
It's asking for the what, the where, the how, and the why.

1775
02:43:17,817 --> 02:43:21,738
so we can answer the questions or end the discussion.

1776
02:43:23,119 --> 02:43:45,667
But right now, the proof that we've seen, what we've sat through in executive sessions, what we sat through for head of unions coming in front of us, the phone calls we've received from fire, from police, from DPW, the battles that are going on hurting good people that are working hard for this community,

1777
02:43:47,868 --> 02:43:56,215
and the fear tactics, and the low morale that's now in this workforce.

1778
02:43:57,816 --> 02:43:59,497
This is why we need this information.

1779
02:44:03,981 --> 02:44:06,183
Because I've heard it over and over again, I'm sure you all have too.

1780
02:44:07,524 --> 02:44:16,371
When the mayor presents the fact that she's here to save the city from the bad employees that were brought in from the prior administration,

1781
02:44:17,278 --> 02:44:18,058
That's getting old.

1782
02:44:20,119 --> 02:44:20,859
That's getting old.

1783
02:44:20,959 --> 02:44:43,503
We're here, we're in this position right now where we're hurting financially because our mayor didn't do anything but fight developers on projects that are happening now, three, four years ago, that she fought in court, lost in court, appealed, lost, but got to a point where those developers just couldn't wait anymore, they moved on.

1784
02:44:44,811 --> 02:44:48,332
They're growing communities like Watertown and Waltham and Malden.

1785
02:44:51,573 --> 02:44:56,474
So, Mr. President, I will not, I will stick with the original plan.

1786
02:44:57,054 --> 02:45:13,718
I will ask my colleagues to sign this document tonight, hand this to the clerk and move this on for a full request for Freedom of Information Act for what we've requested and what we've been asking for, again, because I cannot

1787
02:45:14,885 --> 02:45:20,328
I cannot vote on this year's budget until we see all of the why, the how, and the where.

1788
02:45:20,808 --> 02:45:21,849
So thank you, Mr. President.

1789
02:45:22,950 --> 02:45:23,870
Thank you, Councilor Scarpelli.

1790
02:45:23,890 --> 02:45:24,511
Councilor Sang.

1791
02:45:25,211 --> 02:45:26,392
Thank you, Mr. President.

1792
02:45:27,152 --> 02:45:34,516
Look, I think a lot has been said about this online and in the press.

1793
02:45:35,197 --> 02:45:37,858
Lots of accusations being thrown.

1794
02:45:38,839 --> 02:45:43,862
But at its core, I think this is a pretty straightforward request, and I hope we can treat it that way.

1795
02:45:45,220 --> 02:45:48,748
I don't see this as being about personalities or politics.

1796
02:45:49,008 --> 02:45:51,313
I think it's about oversight and good governance.

1797
02:45:53,358 --> 02:45:56,104
I think it's the type of work that we all came here to do.

1798
02:45:57,013 --> 02:46:08,276
When we see these legal disputes accumulate, when we see labor conflicts drag on, when we see costs mount without clear public accounting, that has real consequences.

1799
02:46:08,536 --> 02:46:22,539
It has real consequences for taxpayers, for government, and for the people who do the work of the city every day, for the people working at City Hall and the DPW and our police stations and fire stations and our schools.

1800
02:46:23,199 --> 02:46:26,520
And I think it's reasonable, and I'd say it's our job,

1801
02:46:27,801 --> 02:46:31,204
for the council to ask for a clearer picture of that and to get a response.

1802
02:46:33,005 --> 02:46:37,209
This isn't really about assigning blame, it's about understanding where we are.

1803
02:46:38,045 --> 02:46:44,410
identifying whether there are lessons that we can draw from this, and making sure that we're managing public resources thoughtfully.

1804
02:46:44,971 --> 02:46:54,838
Because every dollar that's spent on an avoidable conflict is a dollar that's not going to our schools, our streets, our city services.

1805
02:46:55,599 --> 02:47:02,164
And every dispute that we can resolve more effectively strengthens City Hall as a whole as well.

1806
02:47:03,125 --> 02:47:07,567
I also want to say I'm not signing on to something like this lightly.

1807
02:47:08,288 --> 02:47:15,791
I value the working relationships we have across the hall, across city government, including with this administration.

1808
02:47:16,992 --> 02:47:20,934
But I signed on to this precisely because I think this is a request that's measured.

1809
02:47:21,194 --> 02:47:22,114
I think it's reasonable.

1810
02:47:22,794 --> 02:47:32,339
I think it's consistent with the basic principles of what government is supposed to be doing and how we run a good government that's accountable and transparent to the people.

1811
02:47:33,619 --> 02:47:35,780
We're not asking for privileged information.

1812
02:47:36,241 --> 02:47:39,223
We're not trying to relitigate old disputes.

1813
02:47:39,343 --> 02:47:42,505
We're just asking for information that helps all of us plan.

1814
02:47:44,807 --> 02:47:48,709
We've heard it said a lot in this chamber that sunlight is the best disinfectant.

1815
02:47:49,890 --> 02:47:52,192
Transparency shouldn't be something that we fear.

1816
02:47:52,292 --> 02:48:00,357
It should be something that helps this council, helps the administration, helps our employees and the public do a better job running the city together.

1817
02:48:02,333 --> 02:48:06,697
This is constructive, it's not adversarial, and I hope we can receive it in that spirit.

1818
02:48:06,978 --> 02:48:07,318
Thank you.

1819
02:48:10,521 --> 02:48:11,562
Thank you, Councilor Sang.

1820
02:48:13,965 --> 02:48:25,096
And I don't intend to undercut your message with mine, but I think when something is presented like this, requesting

1821
02:48:26,559 --> 02:48:36,982
pretty simple question, how much money have we spent on lawyers and lawsuits and litigation and settlements when we lose most of the time?

1822
02:48:38,483 --> 02:48:48,746
And what is the prudent and effective strategy or lack thereof that we're following as a city when it comes to those questions?

1823
02:48:48,786 --> 02:48:53,748
And is it worth it for our community to be in a constant

1824
02:48:55,398 --> 02:49:09,086
battle where the people who work for the city and the people who run the city are just constantly fighting and can't work together as a team and are afraid to speak out or afraid to speak up or afraid to speak their mind.

1825
02:49:10,847 --> 02:49:24,636
That I think is a question of judgment and a question of leadership and I think if we can't even get the answer to the question how much money did we spend on this, how often are we winning, how often are we losing, how many of these things could have been avoided if we'd taken a different approach.

1826
02:49:25,932 --> 02:49:28,473
I think that's a question that a lot of people have.

1827
02:49:28,513 --> 02:49:33,075
It's a question that I have and it's something that needs to be answered.

1828
02:49:33,175 --> 02:49:38,537
So I agree that I think those should be pretty simple questions to answer.

1829
02:49:39,077 --> 02:49:44,780
And I think we should, if we are doing a good job, we should be able to have that discussion right here in the room.

1830
02:49:45,900 --> 02:49:54,464
And I especially think that when the response to a resolution like this is to

1831
02:49:56,307 --> 02:50:13,316
talk about elections and talk about who, which counselor is working with which other counselor to take me down, or the fact that there's been more things filed since we filed this resolution, and that there are more issues now than there were two months ago.

1832
02:50:14,496 --> 02:50:17,858
And there's no job posting on the city website for a city solicitor.

1833
02:50:17,878 --> 02:50:23,941
It's not even posted to find someone, at least it wasn't when I looked last week.

1834
02:50:26,308 --> 02:50:48,181
And I hope it goes up and I hope we find someone, but it seems like the continued approach that is not working for most people, that is creating strife and conflict, and until we see otherwise is costing the city money, is the path that we're gonna continue to go on.

1835
02:50:49,261 --> 02:50:55,105
And to be frank, I think there's news today that underlines this more than anything about how selective

1836
02:50:55,906 --> 02:50:57,847
this approach is.

1837
02:50:57,987 --> 02:51:03,230
There were residents who filed today in federal court to defend the ordinances of the city of Medford.

1838
02:51:04,131 --> 02:51:11,856
Every single elected official in this city takes an oath to defend the ordinances of the city of Medford.

1839
02:51:12,396 --> 02:51:18,800
And it's literally an open question right now whether the mayor and the city are going to defend the ordinances of the city of Medford.

1840
02:51:19,551 --> 02:51:25,813
to the point that residents had to file in court to defend the ordinances, because they don't know if the city's gonna do it.

1841
02:51:27,774 --> 02:51:46,901
So when there's something that the mayor agrees with, and she wants to pursue something to the end, like suing affordable housing developers for 40B projects, that goes for years in court and delays affordable housing and housing projects that would help the city revenue by years.

1842
02:51:48,108 --> 02:52:16,555
But when there's something the mayor doesn't agree with, like an ordinance that says we don't think we should invest a part of the city's cash reserves in weapons manufacturers, we think about just not defending the ordinances of the city of Medford in federal court and letting someone who sues define what the laws of this city are by their opinion and not the democratically elected opinion of this city government by our charter and by the laws and constitution of the commonwealth.

1843
02:52:18,067 --> 02:52:21,768
That is not a prudent and effective litigation strategy.

1844
02:52:22,269 --> 02:52:23,809
That is not good government.

1845
02:52:24,289 --> 02:52:31,072
And if we can't even answer the question, how much have we spent in the last five years on outside lawyers and settlements?

1846
02:52:32,152 --> 02:52:45,237
You know, I don't care, you know, when a vehicle hits another vehicle, if someone crashes into or a fire truck bumps another vehicle and that costs the city $3,000, that's a normal thing.

1847
02:52:45,978 --> 02:52:46,618
When there are...

1848
02:52:47,410 --> 02:52:51,771
dozens of employment settlements for tens of thousands of dollars.

1849
02:52:54,912 --> 02:53:04,275
And when there are other issues where you just have workers of this city basically saying, my rights have not been respected, that's a different story.

1850
02:53:06,856 --> 02:53:09,317
I just don't think the strategy is prudent and effective.

1851
02:53:09,737 --> 02:53:11,138
I don't think it's serving the residents.

1852
02:53:11,578 --> 02:53:23,782
And I think we need to be able to answer some of the very simple questions included in this ordinance if we're gonna continue to justify the approach that's being taken on legal and contract matters in this city.

1853
02:53:24,282 --> 02:53:29,044
So that's my tune here on this.

1854
02:53:29,144 --> 02:53:35,446
And it maybe is a little different than what some of my fellow colleagues said, but I'm pretty much at my wits end here.

1855
02:53:37,453 --> 02:53:39,515
I just don't think this is working for the city.

1856
02:53:41,877 --> 02:53:42,197
Thank you.

1857
02:53:43,298 --> 02:53:45,260
Any further discussion by members of the council?

1858
02:53:49,283 --> 02:53:57,190
On the motion to approve by Councilor Sang, seconded by Councilor Scarpelli, is there any discussion by members of the public?

1859
02:53:59,532 --> 02:54:02,114
Please raise your hand on Zoom or approach the podium in person.

1860
02:54:04,673 --> 02:54:08,596
Start at the podium, name and address for the record, please, and you'll have three minutes.

1861
02:54:09,457 --> 02:54:11,819
Sure, Micah Kesselman, 499 Main Street.

1862
02:54:14,100 --> 02:54:34,016
Like Council President Bares alluded to, many of you may have heard that this morning there's an announcement that a cohort of residents of the city intend to intervene and enter into the defense of

1863
02:54:35,428 --> 02:54:44,491
the city with regards to the Chairtook v. City of Medford lawsuit raised against it.

1864
02:54:46,332 --> 02:54:50,813
Well, the good news is that lawsuit or that intervention has indeed been filed.

1865
02:54:52,774 --> 02:55:03,537
And it's interesting that you talk a little bit about this issue of having an absence of city solicitor and city representation.

1866
02:55:04,905 --> 02:55:05,645
and legal counsel.

1867
02:55:07,786 --> 02:55:22,911
What you may not know is that when a lawsuit is filed or a motion is filed or really any sort of pleading is put into a case, it has to go through, usually it's filed through an electronic court docket system.

1868
02:55:22,971 --> 02:55:25,092
It's called CMECF.

1869
02:55:25,212 --> 02:55:27,273
It automates a lot of the

1870
02:55:28,252 --> 02:55:39,035
core components of performing the filings of a case, like providing service of motions and pleadings to parties in a dispute.

1871
02:55:40,376 --> 02:55:53,340
It turns out that in cases where one of the parties has not had their counsel make an appearance, it actually becomes impossible to

1872
02:55:54,485 --> 02:56:02,908
have that automatically provide service to the council or to that party in the dispute, which is really unfortunate.

1873
02:56:03,148 --> 02:56:10,331
And that's really because the city doesn't have an active city solicitor and it doesn't seem to have assigned an attorney out of that case, which is too bad.

1874
02:56:11,591 --> 02:56:13,072
It doesn't seem right to me.

1875
02:56:13,412 --> 02:56:14,472
I'm not the city's attorney.

1876
02:56:14,492 --> 02:56:15,453
I'm not the city's council.

1877
02:56:16,493 --> 02:56:21,895
However, I am co-council for the cohort of Medford residents that filed this

1878
02:56:22,633 --> 02:56:24,334
litigation this afternoon.

1879
02:56:25,275 --> 02:56:40,548
And I am co-counsel with the Arab American Anti-Discrimination Committee that is representing on the case, as well as a pro bono attorney from New York who's very accomplished and has done many intervention cases similar to this one.

1880
02:56:41,449 --> 02:56:48,115
And one of the things I would like to present to the council is, counselors, if you could please hand this to

1881
02:56:49,709 --> 02:56:56,234
and that should constitute actually service on the city of our motion to intervene in this litigation.

1882
02:56:56,914 --> 02:56:57,515
