2184
03:25:24,593 --> 03:25:26,314
26084, submitted by Mayor Brianne Alingo-Kern.

2185
03:25:26,334 --> 03:25:31,417
Amendments to the Personnel Ordinance, Director of Elections, Director of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, Director of Veterans Services.

2186
03:25:32,082 --> 03:25:50,370
Dear President Behrs and city councilors, I respectfully request and recommend the city council approve following amendments to the revised ordinances chapter 66 entitled personnel, article 2 entitled reserve, city's classification and compensation plan formally included as article 2 section 6631 to 6640 by adopting the following changes effective July 1, 2026.

2187
03:25:51,231 --> 03:25:58,334
As the council is aware, as part of the city's recent compensation and classification study, we have identified several direct level positions

2188
03:25:58,825 --> 03:26:03,156
that appear to be misaligned with appropriate salary classifications when compared to similarly structured communities.

2189
03:26:03,697 --> 03:26:08,209
Specifically, this review indicates that a certain department head roles are currently placed below market average for positions.

2190
03:26:08,667 --> 03:26:11,189
with comparable scope, responsibility, and organizational impact.

2191
03:26:11,609 --> 03:26:16,592
Because these positions function as department heads, they would typically be aligned with that salary levels above the current classification.

2192
03:26:16,612 --> 03:26:18,433
The market analysis confirmed that.

2193
03:26:18,493 --> 03:26:24,257
In peer communities, the roles are consistently classified and compensated at a higher level than is currently reflected in the city's salary structure.

2194
03:26:24,697 --> 03:26:32,462
To promote internal equity, market competitiveness, and appropriate recognition of departmental leadership, we're recommending adjustments to their classifications and corresponding salary ranges.

2195
03:26:32,903 --> 03:26:36,145
Amendment A, language of CAF 12, shall be amended to remove elections manager.

2196
03:26:36,645 --> 03:26:40,407
and the language of CAF 14 shall be amended to include the following position, Director of Elections.

2197
03:26:41,007 --> 03:26:54,673
Amendment B, the language of CAF 13 shall be amended to remove the following positions, and the language of CAF 15 shall be amended to include the following positions, Director of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, Director of Veteran Services, HR Director Lisa Crowley will be available to speak to these requests, respectfully submitted.

2198
03:26:55,197 --> 03:26:56,557
Brianna Lungo Kern, Mayor.

2199
03:26:57,298 --> 03:27:08,880
We did receive over the weekend a copy of the classification and compensation job descriptions and kind of an explanation of how that study proceeded.

2200
03:27:08,900 --> 03:27:15,922
I think it'd be really good if we scheduled a meeting to really go over the results of the classification and compensation study.

2201
03:27:16,762 --> 03:27:24,784
We did also receive a message from the Chair of the Board of Election Commissioners regarding the

2202
03:27:25,444 --> 03:27:36,529
elections commission, sorry, elections director, elections manager proposed to be director of elections to modify that that should be at CAF 15 instead of CAF 14.

2203
03:27:36,789 --> 03:27:43,492
So it's treated the same as all of the other departments here, the veterans services officer and director of DEI.

2204
03:27:44,773 --> 03:27:49,115
So that's something I think we'd need to discuss further whether we have the authority to do that.

2205
03:27:49,175 --> 03:27:51,076
I think maybe only the mayor has the authority to do that.

2206
03:27:52,076 --> 03:27:53,897
And I'm gonna editorialize for one second.

2207
03:27:54,321 --> 03:28:05,788
which is that in 2022, when we voted to create a separate Department of Elections, I recommended that we have a Director of Elections position at a Director of Elections pay.

2208
03:28:06,128 --> 03:28:09,490
And I think that's a really good thing for us to do now in 2026.

2209
03:28:09,930 --> 03:28:11,331
We've had turnover in that role.

2210
03:28:12,091 --> 03:28:13,832
I think we have a great person in that role.

2211
03:28:13,893 --> 03:28:16,074
I think that has been a department head since day one.

2212
03:28:16,094 --> 03:28:18,355
It should have been treated as a department head since day one.

2213
03:28:20,116 --> 03:28:26,186
I personally am not surprised that the study showed that this department head job should be a department head job.

2214
03:28:26,607 --> 03:28:31,215
So with that, I will go to Councilor Scarpelli and then Vice President Lazaro.

2215
03:28:32,498 --> 03:28:37,200
Thank you, Mr. President, and I don't know if you stole my notes, but that's not fair.

2216
03:28:40,501 --> 03:28:56,586
Again, when we're talking about compensation and retaining great leaders, and that's something that we're seeing difficulties here in the city of Medford in keeping, I think that we have a big turnover when you talk about department heads.

2217
03:28:57,747 --> 03:29:00,888
And we've seen our share in the elections department.

2218
03:29:01,965 --> 03:29:03,326
I think you hit the nail on the head.

2219
03:29:03,346 --> 03:29:16,218
I don't know if it's our place, but I would strongly recommend that we ask our HR director and the mayor to sit down and align all three positions to CAP 15.

2220
03:29:17,159 --> 03:29:26,308
I think that will go a long way in showing all three of our leaders, department leaders,

2221
03:29:27,295 --> 03:29:31,137
We support what they're doing and they should be compensated as such.

2222
03:29:32,958 --> 03:29:48,705
I will, on a personal level, I was a negotiating team in a neighboring community that also did a wage analysis study and one consensus was when we got, when we had positions at this level,

2223
03:29:49,415 --> 03:30:08,289
that we look to align everybody at that same level for the fact that it really showed the fairness and the worth of every single leader that they'd be compensated at that level.

2224
03:30:08,369 --> 03:30:18,657
So as one counselor, I've sat through those meetings and I understand and celebrate the fact that we've done this here in Medford.

2225
03:30:19,328 --> 03:30:24,790
But again, I don't know our authority that we could ask to change that and make the motion to do that.

2226
03:30:25,770 --> 03:30:27,611
If that's the case, I would make that motion.

2227
03:30:27,671 --> 03:30:30,351
But maybe it might be before the vote.

2228
03:30:30,852 --> 03:30:36,493
Maybe we take this to a meeting if we don't get, we might get clarity through the HR director.

2229
03:30:37,134 --> 03:30:38,634
Maybe there's a way we can do this.

2230
03:30:40,095 --> 03:30:46,837
But I would make the motion that we align all three positions to CAF 15.

2231
03:30:47,097 --> 03:30:47,817
Thank you, Mr. President.

2232
03:30:48,522 --> 03:30:49,964
Thank you, Vice President Lazaro.

2233
03:30:51,085 --> 03:30:52,546
I was just gonna say a motion to approve.

2234
03:30:52,927 --> 03:30:57,131
So I don't know if we wanna address Councilor Scarpelli's option.

2235
03:30:57,151 --> 03:31:05,160
All right, so I will recognize our HR Director, Lisa Crowley, to share more about the paper and about our question about moving that to CAF 15 instead of CAF 14.

2236
03:31:11,519 --> 03:31:12,580
Thank you, Mr. President.

2237
03:31:13,160 --> 03:31:18,304
Through you to the council, we're hoping that you do support these changes.

2238
03:31:19,285 --> 03:31:27,230
I hear your concern about the new elections director, I should say.

2239
03:31:28,931 --> 03:31:40,780
Moving these positions through the comp and class showed that they're actually being moved to the comparable salary to which they fall under that classification.

2240
03:31:42,015 --> 03:31:44,188
and readjusting at this time might.

2241
03:31:45,288 --> 03:31:48,891
have some equity discrepancies as well.

2242
03:31:48,911 --> 03:32:02,723
I think in the information I sent you a few days ago, we're going to be looking at the whole comp and class as we go through the summer and the fall to see if there's any other adjustments that have to be made.

2243
03:32:03,243 --> 03:32:11,290
But with this adjustment here, it does fall in line with what the comparable communities have right now for us.

2244
03:32:14,902 --> 03:32:22,106
But I'd be happy, you know, and I'm sure the mayor too would be happy to have a different discussion offline if I'm needed.

2245
03:32:22,126 --> 03:32:27,489
All right, I'll go to Councilor Lemming.

2246
03:32:29,851 --> 03:32:35,294
I think we're more likely to retain the elections manager if we move them up to CAF 15.

2247
03:32:38,745 --> 03:32:46,836
I would be interested to see the numbers about what the comparable salaries are, but the fact is that we've had

2248
03:32:48,689 --> 03:32:55,556
I mean, we've gone through two elections managers, at least in the last term.

2249
03:32:55,596 --> 03:32:59,920
We're on our third, who I think is doing a fine job.

2250
03:33:00,020 --> 03:33:06,386
And having that sort of turnover ends up costing us more money in the long run.

2251
03:33:08,584 --> 03:33:24,573
Not to mince words here, but we had somebody who kind of botched some of the counting in the 2023 election and ended up getting somebody to trigger a recount, which cost the city, I mean, what, like $40,000, $50,000?

2252
03:33:30,737 --> 03:33:36,787
Yeah, if we, sorry, colleagues are laughing over there.

2253
03:33:36,807 --> 03:33:37,849
Continue Councillor Lemming.

2254
03:33:38,490 --> 03:33:38,630
What?

2255
03:33:40,851 --> 03:33:58,485
The point is, if we keep going in this pattern where we try to underpay people and encourage them to start finding employment elsewhere, it ends up costing the city a lot more money in the long run.

2256
03:33:58,545 --> 03:34:02,988
So I think we need to retain our current elections manager.

2257
03:34:03,028 --> 03:34:09,153
I think it will ultimately be cheaper for the city to do so, and I'd support the motion to move it up to CAF 15.

2258
03:34:15,125 --> 03:34:15,365
All right.

2259
03:34:16,825 --> 03:34:30,669
Sounds like we have a motion to amend to have the Director of Elections also move to CAF 15 and a motion to approve as amended from Vice President Lazaro.

2260
03:34:32,309 --> 03:34:36,010
Director Crowley, I mean, so you mentioned maybe having another conversation.

2261
03:34:38,778 --> 03:34:48,223
You know, if we were to amend this and approve it as amended, would that be an issue for you guys or is that something that we can or can't do?

2262
03:34:48,243 --> 03:34:50,285
I mean, it is an ordinance, so.

2263
03:34:51,157 --> 03:34:56,341
It does seem like that would be within our authority to amend and approve, but I wanna check with you.

2264
03:34:57,142 --> 03:35:01,626
We could also, I mean, likely this will be approved tonight for first reading and then advertised.

2265
03:35:01,746 --> 03:35:08,672
So you could check in with the administration and then come back before third reading to let us know what the administration's position is.

2266
03:35:08,892 --> 03:35:11,775
But just wanted to lay the options out for you, Director Crowley.

2267
03:35:13,476 --> 03:35:14,457
And I'll recognize you.

2268
03:35:17,968 --> 03:35:19,208
Thank you again, President Piers.

2269
03:35:19,248 --> 03:35:23,629
Yes, again, if we want to have that conversation, we can certainly do that.

2270
03:35:24,810 --> 03:35:31,091
It would result in a low increase to the elections director, however, if we start moving things around right now.

2271
03:35:31,151 --> 03:35:39,033
So I would appreciate us being able to have that conversation beforehand, if at all possible.

2272
03:35:40,277 --> 03:35:48,440
All right, yeah, so it sounds like we're, this is first reading, so third reading would be in probably the May 26th meeting.

2273
03:35:48,500 --> 03:35:55,803
So maybe we can get an update from you before then and you can let us know what the issue would be by then.

2274
03:35:55,823 --> 03:35:57,143
Does that sound right?

2275
03:35:59,024 --> 03:35:59,284
All right.

2276
03:36:00,184 --> 03:36:05,046
So we have a motion to approve as amended by Vice President, as amended by Councilor Scarpelli.

2277
03:36:05,246 --> 03:36:06,527
Motion from Vice President Lazaro.

2278
03:36:07,293 --> 03:36:14,356
to approve as amended by Councilor Scarpelli, seconded by Councilor Seng for first reading.

2279
